  "firstAcquaintance": "A descendant of the fallen human royal family, wandering in exile for decades since the kingdom's destruction.",
  "personality": "Impeccably polite, revealing her noble upbringing. However, she habitually defers to others, coming across as somewhat meek.",
  "like": "Ketchup",
  "familiarData": "Born after the demon invasion. In Oru's mother's generation, the kingdom still held ambitions of restoring the human realm.\nBut as the long years passed, by the time Oru grew up, there was no one left in the kingdom with true conviction. They were either dependents with nowhere else to go, or people who had long given up fighting the demon race.\nUpon learning of the Hand of Freedom's victory, Oru sought them out, hoping to gain help to reclaim her kingdom. She was fortunate enough to make contact and reach a cooperation agreement, but the condition was that Oru had to sign a slave contract. During the assassination attempt on the Boar King, Oru realized she lacked the ability to lead the knight order to victory. She willingly submitted and accepted her identity as a slave.\nHaving grown up in a barren region, she experienced a massive culture shock the first time she tasted ketchup-based cuisine. Since joining the guild, she wants to eat ketchup-related dishes at every meal.",
